clog
------------------------------------------
Clog is a filter that colorizes log files.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.6.9-1
  libgcc1-14.4.0-1
  libstdc++6-14.4.0-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.46.1-1
  cmake-4.2.1-1
  cygport-0.37.7-1
  gcc-core-14.4.0-1
  gcc-g++-14.4.0-1
  ninja-1.13.2-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/GothenburgBitFactory/clog

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/GothenburgBitFactory/clog/releases/download/v1.3.0/clog-1.3.0.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack clog-1.3.0-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./clog-1.3.0-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/clog-1.3.0-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/clog-1.3.0-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(clog)
  /usr/bin/clog.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/clog.README
  /usr/share/doc/clog/AUTHORS
  /usr/share/doc/clog/COPYING
  /usr/share/doc/clog/ChangeLog
  /usr/share/doc/clog/INSTALL
  /usr/share/doc/clog/LICENSE
  /usr/share/doc/clog/NEWS
  /usr/share/doc/clog/README
  /usr/share/man/man1/clog.1.gz

